Guy Judah (born c. 1986), known by his stage name Guy J, is an Israeli progressive house, techno and electro music producer and DJ who has released three albums and over 15 EPs since 2008.
In July 2012, he founded the imprint record label Lost & Found, supported by the British DJ and producer John Digweed.
Born in Tel Aviv, as of 2020 he is based in Gozo in Malta.
Guy J began DJing at 15 years, and released his debut album Esperanza in 2007 aged 21, on Digweed's Bedrock label.
